There are currently 805 accessible lockers, but there are a total of 4026 students who require lockers. Because only one student can access their locker at a time, the maximum number of students who are required to share a locker is 4026 minus 805, which is 3221. This is the maximum number of students that can be required to share a locker. As a result, the maximum number of students who are compelled to share a locker is 3221. 